---
import TombolaCalculator from "@/components/TombolaCalculator.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main class="flex flex-col gap-8">
    <article class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl text-neutral-100">Tombola Calculator</h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 max-w-[70ch] leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Tombola</strong> is a traditional Italian board game, very popular
        during the Christmas holidays. This calculator helps you distribute the prize pool
        fairly among various prizes following the traditional progressive halving method.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4 max-w-[70ch]">
        <h2 class="text-lg text-neutral-100 mb-2">How it works:</h2>
        <ul class="text-neutral-300 text-sm space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>Tombola:</strong> The biggest prize, minimum 6 cartelle (covers the tombolone's buy-in)</li>
          <li><strong>Cinquina:</strong> Five numbers in the same row</li>
          <li><strong>Quaterna:</strong> Four numbers in the same row</li>
          <li><strong>Terna:</strong> Three numbers in the same row</li>
          <li><strong>Ambo:</strong> Two numbers in the same row, minimum 1 cartella (covers the player's buy-in)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs mt-3">
          A <em>cartella</em> is the playing card. The <em>tombolone</em> (number caller) traditionally must buy 6 cartelle.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article>
      <TombolaCalculator />
    </article>

    <article class="flex flex-col gap-4 max-w-[70ch]">
      <h2 class="text-xl text-neutral-100">Important Notes</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Smart Distribution:</strong> When you set a cartella price, the calculator requires a minimum
        prize pool to cover 7 cartelle (6 for tombolone + 1 for at least one player). It ensures Ambo winners
        recover at least their entry cost and Tombola winners cover the tombolone's buy-in. The remaining
        prize pool is distributed with weighted proportions ensuring each prize is progressively larger.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Divisibility:</strong> All prizes are rounded to multiples of 20 cents to ensure they can be
        evenly divided between two winners (a common case in Tombola games). This
        ensures easy distribution with real coins (10, 20, 50 cents, 1 and 2 euros).
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Any remainder is distributed proportionally among all prizes, maintaining
        the exact total of the initial prize pool.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
